President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of North Carolina following severe winter storms and flooding that occurred from December 18-25, 2009. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Michael Bolch has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.